INSERT INTO `tb_test_item` VALUES ('1841', '<p>Question 196- 200 refer to the following e-mail messages</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Date: January 3</p>\r\n<p>To: Donna Rockefeller, Floral &amp; Decorations &lt;drockefeller@floraldeco.net&gt;</p>\r\n<p>From: Sinclair Peterson &lt;manager@canadaflowers.ca&gt;</p>\r\n<p>Subject: Order #545- carnations shipped</p>\r\n<p>Good to hear from you again. Thank you for ordering another shipment from Canada Flowers. I have shipped 5 boxes of carnations to your office in New York by Speed Delivery, which should arrive over the next day or so. Unfortunately, because of high demand, I could only send you five of the eight boxes you requested since the carnations have completely sold out. That was the last shipment this year from our warehouse, which is in Montreal.</p>\r\n<p>To be honest, I have never experienced carnation sales like this during my twenty- year career in the flower industry. I beileve that it is due to a recent television show that described our garden as having the best quality flowers in any of Thunder Bay ’ s gardens. Since that television show, I have struggled to keep up with the growing demand for carnations in all colors and types.</p>\r\n<p>If you still need to recieve the addtional boxes of carnations, please contact me as soon as possible. I have a colleague who owns a large flower distribution center, called Plants, Ltd. </p>\r\n<p>I look forward to speaking with you in the near future.</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>S. Perterson</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Date: January 5</p>\r\n<p>To: Chad Jackson, Plants, Ltd.</p>\r\n<p>From: Sinclair Peterson, Canada Flowers </p>\r\n<p>Subject: Request for Possible Carnations</p>\r\n<p>Hello Chad,</p>\r\n<p>I hope everything is good with you. I have just run out of the last of my carnations and I still have some orders to fill. I know that you are in a very busy season at the moment, but is there any possibility that you have any extra carnations in stock I can buy? If you do, I would be very grateful if they could be sent to my ware house. I will phone you later this afternoon to discuss payment and other details.</p>\r\n<p>Do you think that you will be able to make it to the grand opening of my new store in March? I haven ’ t seen you for a long time and I would love to have you there.</p>\r\n<p>Looking forward to speaking with you shortly.</p>\r\n<p>S.Peterson</p>', '9', '11', '1', 'She has ordered from Canada Flowers before', 'She works in Thunder Bay', 'She is the host of a television program', 'She knows someone who works for Canada Flowers', '<p><strong>What does the first e- mail indicate about Ms. Rockefeller?</strong></p>', '196', '0', '1', '1', 'vi', '1', '2015-11-30 12:29:33', '2015-11-30 15:13:48');
